Below is a brief outline of subjects covered in this course that i studied over a 3 month period to get familiar with the Fundamentals to establish a base foundation of knowledge before proceeding.

The course included:

 1. Important IT Concepts
      Computing devices & hardware basics
      Software and operating systems overview
      Types of software (application, etc.)

  2. Servers and Virtualization
      Physical servers
      Virtualization concepts
      AWS account setup & walkthrough (hands-on lab)

  3. Data Center & Cloud Computing Overview
      Data center fundamentals
      Cloud computing basics
      Cloud service models (IaaS, PaaS, SaaS)
      Deployment models (public, private, hybrid)
      Choosing a cloud provider

4. Networking Fundamentals
      What is a network
      Traffic flow types
      Wired & wireless devices
      Network cabling
      Data center networks  
      Campus area networks
      The internet

5. IP Addressing Deep Dive
      IP address need, structure & formats
      Binary & decimal conversions
      Networks & hosts
      Subnet masks & subnetting
      Assignment - Subnet mask assignments
      Assignment - Subnetting assignments
      IP classes & ranges
      Public vs private IPs
      Assignment - IP scheme design assignments   

  6. IP Routing & AWS Networking
      How IP routing works
      Packet structure
      AWS global infrastructure
      VPC, subnets, route tables
      Internet gateway & NAT
      AWS - AWS networking demos - Public subnets, Private subets and NAT in AWS VPC

  7. OSI & TCP/IP Models + Protocols
      OSI model & layers
      TCP/IP model
      Core protocols (ICMP, SSH, HTTP/HTTPS)
      Packet anatomy
      SSH demos (Windows/Linux)

  8. Cybersecurity & Network Security Fundamentals
      Cybersecurity basics
      Firewalls & AWS security groups
      Network ACLs (NACLs)
      Encryption
      VPN fundamentals
      AWS - VPC security groups & SSH/ICMP/HTTP testing

  9. DNS, Databases & Monitoring
      DNS (Domain Name System)
      Monitoring, alerting, logging
      Databases & SQL basics
      Architecture diagramming

  10. Additional Sections
      Linux & Bash basics
      DevOps tools overview (Git, Docker, Kubernetes, Terraform)
